		<htmltext><![CDATA[
			<h3><strong>Approval of electric vehicles</strong></h3>		
			<p><b>Application</b></p>
			<p>The manufacturer, or its duly accredited representative, 
			shall submit the application of approval of a vehicle type. A document with 
			detailed description of the vehicle type with regard to the electric power train and 
			galvanically connected high voltage bus and a document which shows additional evidence 
			that the RESS, if used in the vehicle, complies with the regulation. A vehicle representative 
			of the vehicle type to be approved shall be submitted to the Technical Service responsible for 
			conducting the approval tests. If the Technical Service find extra vehicles or specific parts 
			essential for the testing, they can be ask from the manufacturer.</p>
			<p><b>Approcval</b></p>
			<p>Before type approval is granted the Type Approval Authority shall verify the existence 
			of satisfactory arrangements for ensuring effective control of the conformity of production.</p>
			<p>Approval shall be granted if the submitted vehicle meets the relevant requirements  and 
			the approved type shall be given an approval number . The approval authority communicates 
			the outcome of the application for approval via a standard document to the manufacturer. 
			This document gives in case of approval, information to which regulation the vehicle is approved, 
			the country which granted the approval.  The given approval mark shall be clearly readable and permanent 
			placed on or close to the vehicle data plate.</p>
			<p><b>Modifications and extension on type approval</b></p>
			<p>Every modification with regard to the approval regulation shall be notified to the approval 
			authority. The approval authority decides if further tests are necessary.</p>
		]]></htmltext>
